{
    "name": "Prophet of Baphomet",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> temperate ruins or underground"
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Just as minotaurs believe they\u2019re direct descendants of Baphomet, minotaur prophets consider themselves his ideal mortal servitors. Prophets favor cunning gambits and manipulation over direct confrontation, and toy with captives and even their own cultists. Prophets also honor the Lord of the Labyrinth\u2019s more bestial interests; worshipers and enemies alike often fall victim to a prophet\u2019s monstrous appetite for flesh."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>This white-maned minotaur\u2019s gilt-edged robes project elegance and terror in equal measure. The cloud of heady incense about her form doesn\u2019t conceal the distinct scent of brimstone.</i>",
